article.headline: N. Colorado 88, N. Arizona 86
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. (AP) -- Jefferson Mason's rebound and layup with 10 seconds left to play lifted Northern Colorado to an 88-86 win over Northern Arizona Thursday night. Northern Colorado (3-14, 1-4 Big Sky) and Northern Arizona (8-8, 3-2) were tied 10 times and exchanged the lead as many times as the Bears won their first Big Sky Conference game. Northern Arizona took an 86-82 lead 3:45 remaining in the game, but the Lumberjacks were unable to score the rest of the way. Ruben Boykin Jr. missed a 3-pointer with 4 seconds remaining and Tyrone Bazy's rebound and jumper missed the mark as time expired. Sean Tiabi led the Bears with 26 points, while Kirk Archibeque added 23 points. Mason finished with 11 points and four rebounds. Stephen Sir led Northern Arizona with 30 points and Ruben Boykin Jr. scored 22 points. Bazy added 13 points for the Lumberjacks.
